Spanish--Spanish Sign Language translator
===================================================================

The LSE/SSL side of this translator uses the  Sistema de Escritura 
Alfabético (SEA) as described in:

Ángel Herrera (2003) "Escritura alfabética de la lengua de 
  signos española" (Alicante: UA)

It is also covered on the Wiki (in Spanish): 

  http://wiki.apertium.org/wiki/Traductor_de_español_a_LSE

===================================================================

TRANSLATOR

You need apertium and lttoolbox version 3.0, to use
this language-pair package with Apertium.  To compile the linguistical
data simply do:

$ ./configure

to generate a Makefile file and then

$ make

inside of this directory.

===================================================================

More information about this module, and others can be found on 
the Apertium: Wiki, http://wiki.apertium.org

